    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "Is sedation required?",
        "answer": "Rarely. If you have severe claustrophobia, oral sedation can be arranged at no added cost.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "When will reports be ready?",
        "answer": "Final radiologist-signed report and cloud link within 24 hours.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I eat before the scan?",
        "answer": "Fast 4 hours to reduce bowel movement artefacts; water is allowed.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": " What if the MRI Whole Body scan highlights an unexpected issue?",
        "answer": "If any significant or unexpected findings are discovered, our team at Cadabams Diagnostics ensures the report provides clear information. Your doctor will explain the findings to you and recommend the most appropriate next steps, which could involve more specific imaging or consultation with a specialist."
      },
      {
        "question": "How much does an MRI Whole Body scan cost at Cadabams Diagnostics?",
        "answer": "The **MRI whole body scan cost** can vary based on several factors, including whether a contrast agent is needed. For the most accurate and up-to-date pricing information, please contact Cadabams Diagnostics directly or visit our website's pricing section. "
      },
      {
        "question": "Will I need contrast dye for my MRI Whole Body Scan?",
        "answer": "Many screening whole body MRI scans are performed without contrast. However, if the scan is being done to investigate a specific problem or if an abnormality is seen, a contrast agent may be needed for better diagnostic clarity. Our medical team will discuss this with you beforehand if it applies to your situation."
      }
