    "markdown": "## Whole Body MRI – An Overview\n\n### What the whole body MRI package covers\n- High-resolution images of 6 major body regions\n- 1.5 Tesla Siemens scanner for crisp detail\n- Complimentary radiologist consult & 24-hour digital report\n### Why Cadabams Diagnostics is preferred\n- 35+ years of diagnostics legacy in South India\n- Same-day appointment flexibility\n- Transparent, all-inclusive pricing—no hidden contrast charges\n## What Is MRI Whole Body?\n### Definition and technology behind whole body MRI\nMagnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) uses powerful magnets and radio waves to create cross-sectional images. In a \\*\\*MRI Whole Body\\*\\*, the table moves continuously while multiple coils capture data, stitching together a full anatomical map.\n### Difference from targeted or contrast MRI\n- No dye injection in the standard protocol—ideal for screening\n- Covers entire body rather than one organ\n- Zero ionising radiation compared with CT whole body scans\n\n## Risks & Limitations of MRI Whole Body Scan\n\n### Low-risk procedure with no radiation exposure\n- MRI is regarded as one of the safest imaging modalities\n- No known biological hazards at 1.5 T field strength\n### Limitations: small-lesion detection, claustrophobia, metal implants\n- Lesions <5 mm may need targeted follow-up\n- Tight scanner bore can trigger anxiety (open-bore option available)\n- Pacemakers, cochlear implants, certain aneurysm clips are contraindicated\n\n## MRI Whole Body Parameters Considered\n\n### Brain, spine, and musculoskeletal review\n- White-matter changes, disc herniations, marrow infiltration\n### Chest & abdominal organs, pelvis, soft-tissue masses\n- Liver, pancreas, kidneys, prostate/uterus, lymph-node stations\n\n## When to Take Test\n\n### Early detection of tumours, aneurysms, inflammation\n- Spot solid-organ cancers at Stage 1\n- Identify aortic aneurysms before rupture\n### Baseline health mapping before lifestyle changes\n- Document pre-diet visceral fat levels\n- Compare annual progress objectively\n\n## Benefits of Whole Body MRI\n\n- Single-session full-body scan—no need for multiple appointments\n- No radiation, high-resolution imaging\n- Digital report within 24 hours—share instantly with any specialist\n\n## Conditions Diagnosed with Whole Body MRI\n\n- Solid-organ cancers: liver, kidney, pancreas, prostate, breast\n- Vascular anomalies: aneurysms, dissections, AVMs\n- Degenerative spine disease: canal stenosis, disc prolapse\n\n## Preparation for Whole Body MRI Scan\n\n### Pre-requisites: fasting 4 hrs, remove metal objects\n- Light breakfast allowed if booked after 12 pm\n- Leave jewellery, belts and watches at home\n### Best time: morning slots reduce waiting\n- Centre opens 7 am; finish scan before office hours\n### Eligibility: 18+ yrs, BMI ≤35, no pacemaker\n- Weight limit 120 kg for table safety\n## Procedure for Taking a MRI Whole Body\n1. Change into cotton gown; locker for valuables\n2. Lie supine on MRI table; cushions stabilise head & knees\n3. Coil positioning: head, neck, body phased-array\n4. Table moves in 8 stations; machine makes knocking sounds (ear plugs provided)\n5. Total table time: 45-60 minutes\n6. Radiologist reviews images; you leave with a provisional summary\n## Caution Before Taking the Test\n- Inform staff about implants, pregnancy, claustrophobia\n- Open-bore or 3 T wide-bore alternatives available on request"
